      "name": "BL - Brand Review",
      "settings": {
        "section_id": "brand-3",
        "bg_color": "#faf9f7",
        "number": "#3",
        "badge_text": "",
        "brand_name": "Meroda Cosmetics",
        "rating": "4.2",
        "price_text": "$36.00",
        "review_text": "<p>Meroda's color-changing foundation has an eye-catching transformation — the white-to-color shift is dramatic and fun to watch. But once the novelty wears off, the results are mixed. The shade it settled on was close to my skin tone but not exact, with a slightly ashy finish that needed correcting with powder.</p><p>The formula is thinner than the others, which sounds good in theory but meant it didn't provide enough coverage to even out age spots and discoloration — a common concern for women over 40. It also oxidized noticeably over 4-5 hours, turning a shade darker than where it started.</p><p>At $36.00, it's slightly cheaper than Vera Lane but delivers noticeably less in shade matching and longevity. The color-changing effect is more gimmick than science here.</p>",
        "verdict": "Fun to watch but disappointing to wear. The shade-matching technology isn't refined enough, and the oxidation issue is a dealbreaker for all-day wear.",
        "image_asset": "lp-comparison-foundation-brand-3.jpg",
        "image_position": "right"
      }
    },
