      "name": "BL - Brand Review",
      "settings": {
        "section_id": "brand-4",
        "bg_color": "#faf9f7",
        "number": "#4",
        "badge_text": "",
        "brand_name": "Forever Bloom",
        "rating": "4.3",
        "price_text": "$42.49",
        "review_text": "<p>Forever Bloom's Bio Mimic Foundation has strong Amazon ratings and SPF 50 protection, which is a nice bonus. The color-changing effect works reasonably well — better than Meroda — but it still doesn't match Vera Lane's precision. The shade landed close but slightly off on my skin.</p><p>Where it falls short for mature skin is longevity and texture. Within a few hours, the foundation had visibly settled into fine lines around my eyes and mouth, creating that crepe-paper effect we all dread. The formula also oxidized noticeably by mid-afternoon, shifting to an unflattering warmer tone.</p><p>At $42.49, it's priced higher than Vera Lane without delivering the same level of shade accuracy or comfortable all-day wear. The SPF 50 is genuinely appealing, but not enough to offset the other issues for mature skin.</p>",
        "verdict": "The SPF 50 is a real selling point, but the line-settling and oxidation make it a tough recommendation for mature skin. Vera Lane outperforms it where it matters most.",
        "image_asset": "lp-comparison-foundation-brand-4.jpg",
        "image_position": "left"
      }
    },
